                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/2330</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-10">March 10,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Proposal of peace terms to the German people over the
                    heads of the Nazi Government.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: There is a great deal of agitation of
                    certain groups that before the actual invasion commences this Government should
                    take every possible step in the direction of the surrender of Germany, and the
                    suggestion is being made by certain organized groups that before the actual
                    invasion starts a proposal be made to the German people as a whole over the
                    heads of the Nazi Government.</p>
                <p>I am not sympathetic personally with this point of view, but it is bound to be an
                    active issue in the weeks to come.</p>
                <p>I think it is important that you and the President have your views definitely
                    crystallized on the matter because some day we might have to answer certain
                    criticisms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
